{
  "texts": [
    "A bibliometric analysis is a commonly used method to identify the development of a certain field.",
    "The technique helps to research horizon scanning and quantify research outputs and impact of researchers, research groups, universities, countries, and research fields etc.",
    "(Lancho-Barrantes and Cantu Ortiz, 2019; 2021).",
    "Most importantly, bibliometric analysis is useful to identify gaps in the literature, generate insights into recent trends and developments, and to inform future research direction (Ogunleye et al. 2024).",
    "To this end, this study aims to conduct a bibliometrics analysis of TM to provide an overview of the current state of research on TM, examine the applications of TM and offer insights into future research directions."
  ]
}